16/05/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A new government strategy for Croatia's development through 2013 was introduced on Monday (15 May) at the National Competitiveness Council in Zagreb. Presenting the document, Prime Minister Ivo Sanader said that it cited as priority tasks reducing unemployment from the current 12.7 per cent to 9 per cent by 2010, as well as boosting economic growth beyond 5 per cent by 2013. He stressed that the strategy would seek to achieve social prosperity through development of a market economy, capable of meeting the challenges related to EU membership. (Vecernji list - 16/05/06; HINA, HRT - 15/05/06)
